OL,3,CExtremists who planned 'one of the
OL,4,Cdeadliest terrorist attacks in UK'
OL,5,Cjailed
OL,7,FSaadaoui's brother Bilal, 36, who was
OL,8,Fnot planning to take part in the
OL,9,Fattacks was also convicted after a
OL,10,Fjury believed he knew what was
OL,11,Fhappening yet failed to report it.
OL,13,FJudge Mark Wall KC, referenced
OL,14,FHussein's 'cowardice' after he refused
OL,15,Fto return to the dock for sentencing.
OL,17,FSaadaoui was told by a judge at
OL,18,FPreston Crown Court on Friday that he
OL,19,Fmust serve a minimum of 37 years in
OL,20,Fcustody while Hussein will serve at
OL,21,Fleast 26 years.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/13
